DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);


$x=random(-5,5,2);
$y=random(-6,6,1);
$z=random(-5,5,2);

$r1=$x+$y+$z;
$r2=2*$x-$y+3*$z;
$r3=3*$x+$y-4*$z;



TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 



Solve the following system:

\[
\begin{array}{rcrcrcl}
x &+& y &+& z &=& $r1 \\
2x &-& y &+& 3z &=& $r2 \\
3x &+& y &-& 4z &=& $r3 \\
\end{array}
\]

Keep track of your calculations, because in the next problem you will
have the same system, except that the right hand side is different.

$BR The solution is 

\(x = \)  \{ ans_rule(10) \},
EOT
&ANS( num_cmp($x));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
\(y = \)  \{ ans_rule(10) \},
EOT
&ANS( num_cmp($y));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
\(z = \)  \{ ans_rule(10) \}.
EOT
&ANS( num_cmp($z));






ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
